General aspect.
Blind and unpigmented. Body smooth and clearly ventrally ¯attened. Thickness of the body, at the medio-dorsal line, hardly equivalent to half of the body width. Body shape regular (®gure 1) with pereionite margins parallel, regularly rounded anteriorly at the ®rst pereionite and the cephalon; free pleonites slightly narrower than pereionite 7. Pleotelson subtriangular and widened. Pereionites 2±4 of same length and shorter than following ones. Pereionites 5±7 increasing in length successively; body width equivalent to one-quarter of total length from anterior margin of cephalon to end of pleotelson, from dorsal observation. Female generally longer (
12 mm
